ww.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/22110419/IMG_7735-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/22110419/IMG_7735-768x513.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/22110419/IMG_7735-1536x1026.jpg 1536w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/22110419/IMG_7735-2048x1368.jpg 2048w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/22110419/IMG_7735-696x465.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/22110419/IMG_7735-1068x713.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/22110419/IMG_7735-1920x1283.jpg 1920w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/22110419/IMG_7735-629x420.jpg 629w\"></a></p><h3>What makes the Elite Tuo different?</h3><p>What separates the Elite Tuo from others in the genre is accuracy (for a wheel-on trainer) and the aesthetics (it looks like a piece of furniture and not a trainer). The Tuo comes after indoor racing, and smart trainers had time to settle into settled formats so the company could better address key factors to achieve success in the virtual world.</p><p>The Elite Tuo’s mission is to provide an interactive indoor riding experience on par with direct trainers, at a lower price. The Tuo generates resistance with a magnetic system and connects wirelessly to your computer, phone, or tablet — automatically adjusting resistance to simulate a course or workout.</p><p>One of the advantages of the wheel-on trainer style is that the design is compact, and the Tuo is no different. The resistance unit is highly designed, and from the side, looks nothing like a training tool. Held sturdy by beechwood legs, this trainer is more of a conversation piece than gear you need to store away after a workout — and at $580, it’s priced to be competitive with both wheel-on and direct-drive models.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/22120748/IMG_0588-scaled.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/22120748/IMG_0588-scaled.jpeg\" alt=\"Elite Tuo Trainer Review Mobile desktop \" width=\"2560\" height=\"2396\" sizes=\"(max-width: 2560px) 100vw, 2560px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/22120748/IMG_0588-scaled.jpeg\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/22120748/IMG_0588-scaled.jpeg 2560w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/22120748/IMG_0588-297x278.jpeg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/22120748/IMG_0588-800x749.jpeg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/22120748/IMG_0588-120x112.jpeg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/22120748/IMG_0588-768x719.jpeg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/22120748/IMG_0588-1536x1437.jpeg 1536w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/22120748/IMG_0588-2048x1917.jpeg 2048w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/22120748/IMG_0588-696x651.jpeg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/22120748/IMG_0588-1068x1000.jpeg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/