://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/22135654/Screen-Shot-2021-03-22-at-1.56.13-PM-768x792.png 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/22135654/Screen-Shot-2021-03-22-at-1.56.13-PM-1490x1536.png 1490w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/22135654/Screen-Shot-2021-03-22-at-1.56.13-PM-1986x2048.png 1986w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/22135654/Screen-Shot-2021-03-22-at-1.56.13-PM-696x718.png 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/22135654/Screen-Shot-2021-03-22-at-1.56.13-PM-1068x1101.png 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/22135654/Screen-Shot-2021-03-22-at-1.56.13-PM-1920x1980.png 1920w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/22135654/Screen-Shot-2021-03-22-at-1.56.13-PM-407x420.png 407w\"></a></p><p>The unit has a basic calibration protocol and a solid maintenance plan for keeping it tidy and within the promised tolerances. Elite asks that you pump your tire up to 110psi and warm up the trainer for about 10-15 minutes. You then get off the bike and adjust the contact with the tire and rubber roller wheel. At this point, you adjust the connection, so the tire and roller wheel are just touching without the engagement lever thrown. Once you’re satisfied with the contact, engage the lever and check for max tire and wheel connection. Now you’re all set to perform a calibration roll-down. I found that the one available through Zwift works the best for virtual riding and programmed interval sessions.</p><p>To stay in 5% power accuracy and calibration, Elite asked that you maintain the 110psi pressure in the tire contacting the roller — A relatively simple and easy way to keep on top of the calibration and consistency of the trainer.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/22110358/IMG_7736-scaled.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/22110358/IMG_7736-scaled.jpg\" alt=\"Elite Tuo Trainer Review attachment roller wheel\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1709\" sizes=\"(max-width: 2560px) 100vw, 2560px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/22110358/IMG_7736-scaled.jpg\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/22110358/IMG_7736-scaled.jpg 2560w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/22110358/IMG_7736-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/22110358/IMG_7736-800x534.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/22110358/IMG_7736-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/22110358/IMG_7736-768x513.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/22110358/IMG_7736-1536x1025.jpg 1536w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/22110358/IMG_7736-2048x1367.jpg 2048w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/22110358/IMG_7736-696x465.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/22110358/IMG_7736-1068x713.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/22110358/IMG_7736-1920x1282.jpg 1920w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.ama